    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="589"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/7–2446</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Acheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Deputy Director of the Office of European
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hickerson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-24">July 24,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Hickerson</hi>: I discussed the matter of reviving the
                    project to sell surplus property to the Soviet Union as set forth in your
                        memorandum,<note n="36" xml:id="d589fn36">No copy of a memorandum by Mr.
                        Hickerson found in Department files.</note> with special reference to the
                    need for using some of the proceeds for the betterment of our Embassy staff
                    facilities in Moscow. After going over the matter thoroughly, the Secretary
                    instructed me that he did not wish to raise the matter at this time.</p>
                <p>I have given this information to Mr. McCabe. For your information, Mr. McCabe
                    says that this conclusion accords with the necessities of the case in that (<hi
                        rend="italic">a</hi>) the Soviet Union has not accepted the terms of the
                    credit; (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) it does not wish to acquire any of the
                    property presently declared surplus in Europe; (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) it
                    wishes us to declare additional property surplus; and (<hi rend="italic">d</hi>)
                    it wishes to inspect surplus property in the Pacific.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>D[<hi rend="smallcaps">ean</hi>] A[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >cheson</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
